     fhir:div [ fhir:v "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><p class=\"res-header-id\"><b>Generated Narrative: CodeSystem devicealert-presence</b></p><a name=\"devicealert-presence\"> </a><a name=\"hcdevicealert-presence\"> </a><p>This case-sensitive code system <code>http://hl7.org/fhir/devicealert-presence</code> defines the following codes:</p><table class=\"codes\"><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Display</b></td><td><b>Definition</b></td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">on<a name=\"devicealert-presence-on\"> </a></td><td>On</td><td>The signal is annunciated due to the presence of the alert condition</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">latched<a name=\"devicealert-presence-latched\"> </a></td><td>Latched</td><td>The signal is annunciated after the alert condition is no longer present, until it is stopped by deliberate operator action</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">off<a name=\"devicealert-presence-off\"> </a></td><td>Off</td><td>The signal is not being annunciated and the alert condition is no longer present</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">ack<a name=\"devicealert-presence-ack\"> </a></td><td>Acknowledged</td><td>The signal is no longer annunciated having been stopped by deliberate operator action although the alert condition is still present</td></tr></table></div>"^^rdf:XMLLiteral ]
